Swift Trigger and Burst REAL-TIME Information

This page changes after each Trigger/GRB/Notice, so hit your   <reload>   button NOW.

This table contains information about GRBs (and non-GRBs) detected by Swift (BAT, XRT, and UVOT).
The most recent Notice is listed first in the table (reverse time order).

The 3 left-most columns (GRB/TRIGGER) give the ID number and the date/time of the event.
These columns contain:
      the Trigger Number (which is a link to all the original full-format email GCN/Swift Notices on that trigger),
      the Date (yy/mm/dd), and
      the Time (hh:mm:ss.ss) of the start of the GRB.

The next 20 columns (OBSERVATION) come from the results of the various observations and analysis by the Swift BAT, XRT and UVOT instruments.
These columns contain:
      the BAT RA,Dec Position and error,   XRT RA,Dec Position and error,   UVOT RA,Dec Position and error,
      the BAT LightCurve (links to the 5 std formats, and starting with Trigger=374875 there are 5 Extended LC links),
      XRT LightCurve (links), XRT Spectrum (types 1 and 2, links, both raw files and the post-processed),
      XRT Image (links, both raw files and the post-processed),
      UVOT Source_List (links, both raw files and the post-processed),
      UVOT Image (links, both raw files and the post-processed).
All 3 RA,Dec locations are in J2000 epoch. The error (arcmin or arcsec diameter, systematic+statistical) uncertainty in that location.
If a column's information is not available or is not applicable, then that entry is listed as "n/a" or left blank.

For more information on the 3 Swift instruments: Swift.

Mail questions/suggestions/complaints to Scott Barthelmy.
